  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "To start, finely grate your garlic and 1 knob of ginger into a bowl. Add 2 tbsp mayo, 2 tbsp gochujang and a squeeze of lemon. Mix together and set aside."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Next, heat a glug of oil and fry your pollock until white in colour (for about 2 minutes)."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Once you have fried your pollock, place in a bowl and roughly break it up. Add your breadcrumbs and sauce (prepared in step 1) then mix together so that the fish is fully coated."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Take a handful of this mixture and mould into a patty shape. Repeat until you get 4 patties then set aside ready for frying."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Slice your red cabbage and add to a bowl along with your beansprouts."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "In a separate bowl mix together 3 tbsps of oil, sesame oil, rice vinegar, honey and the other knob of grated ginger. Mix until combined then add this to your red cabbage and mix it through."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "For the burger sauce, mix together 2 tbsp mayo and 1/2 tbsp gochujang then set aside."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Now for your patty. Heat a glug of oil in a pan and fry each patty until crispy and golden brown then remove."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Then, cut your brioche buns in half and toast both sides, then you’re ready to layer up."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Take the base of your brioche bun and add a squeeze of burger sauce, followed by your patty, then a generous handful of cabbage mix. Pop your brioche bun on top and enjoy!"
    }
  ],
